+# Codex Reviewer Findings — ПССК Prompt Quality Review
+Chain: pssk-cv-b2-260416-v10-260416-211945-e22f
+
+## Issues Found
+1. [CRITICAL] Fix 3 creates a TDZ crash by calling `isCancelledOrder` before it exists — Fix 1 tells the executor to introduce `isCancelledOrder` after `tableOrdersTotal` and before `submittedTableTotal` (prompt lines 171-183), while Fix 3 then tells the executor to insert `tableIsClosed` immediately before `ordersSum` and call `isCancelledOrder(o)` there (prompt lines 699-717). In the real file, `ordersSum` is at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:490) and `tableOrdersTotal`/`submittedTableTotal` are later at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:514). A literal implementation therefore references a `const` helper before initialization, which violates the repo’s TDZ rule and can crash render. PROMPT FIX: move `isCancelledOrder` into the shared helper area above all memo consumers, or move `tableIsClosed` below the helper and update the placement instructions and grep anchors accordingly.
+2. [MEDIUM] New memo snippets omit the `getOrderStatus` dependency they rely on — The new Fix 1 memos (`renderedTableTotal`, `renderedTableDishCount`, `renderedTableGuestCount`) and the Fix 3 `tableIsClosed` memo call `isCancelledOrder`, which closes over `getOrderStatus`, but their dependency arrays omit both `getOrderStatus` and the helper. The current file already treats `getOrderStatus` as a memo dependency in comparable places at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:453) and [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:467). If the prop identity changes, the prompt’s literal code can leave stale totals or stale terminal visibility. PROMPT FIX: add `getOrderStatus` to every new dependency array that uses `isCancelledOrder`, or explicitly memoize the helper and depend on that memoized value.
+3. [MEDIUM] Fix 1 does not define the loading-state behavior for dish counts — The prompt replaces the table header with rendered-data metrics based on `itemsByOrder`, but the real table section already has an explicit loading branch when `sessionItems.length === 0 && sessionOrders.length > 0` at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:848) and [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:871). That means item data can lag behind order totals. As written, the prompt can produce a transient header like `Стол: 2 гостя · 0 блюд · 1500₸`, which contradicts the “rendered-data invariant” it is trying to enforce. PROMPT FIX: specify whether the new table header should wait for session items, show a loading placeholder, or temporarily hide dish-count metrics until `itemsByOrder` is populated.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 3 issues (1 CRITICAL, 2 MEDIUM, 0 LOW)
